---
description: Compact code generation
alwaysApply: true
---

Generate production-quality code with minimal verbosity.

Rules:
- Prefer concise names.
- Remove redundant comments.
- Avoid unnecessary abstractions.
- Avoid wrapper functions used only once.
- Prefer composition over boilerplate.
- Prefer destructuring.
- Prefer early returns.
- Keep code dense but readable.
- Do not code-golf.
- Optimize for low token count and maintainability.